1. Build Debian 13 image
   a. Run debian13.sh
   b. Wait for the image, debian13.img

2. Make a bootable USB drive
   a. Run usb-boot.sh
   b. Wait for the image, usb-boot.img
   c. Flash usb-boot.img to a USB drive
      - dd if=usb-boot.img of=/dev/sdb bs=4M status=progress
   d. Resize the data partition
      - parted /dev/sdb
        > print (Choose 'Fix' if prompted) 
        > resizepart 3 100%
        > print (check the size!)
        > quit
      - mkfs.exfat -L data /dev/sdb3
   e. Mount /dev/sdb3 to /media/usb
   e. Copy debian13.img to /media/usb
   f. Copy Android.tar.gz to /media/usb
   h. umount /media/usb

3. Prepare SBC
   a. Boot SBC with the bootable USB
   b. Mount the data partition: mount /dev/sdb3 /media
      - mount /dev/sdb3 /media
   c. cd /media
   d. Flash debian13.img to SBC drive
      - dd if=debian13.img of=/dev/sda bs=4M status=progress
   f. Resize the data partition
      - parted /dev/sda
        > print (Choose 'Fix' if prompted)
        > resizepart 3 100%
        > print (to check the size)
        > quit
      - resize2fs /dev/sda3
   g. Unmount and remove USB
   h. Reboot with the disk drive (/dev/sda)

4. Customize Debian
   a. Suppress gnome warning dialog
      - gsettings set org.gnome.mutter check-alive-timeout 0
   a. Hide top bar
      - Alt-F2
      - Type 'gnome-extensions-app' and enter
      - Enable 'Extensions' and 'Hide-Top-Bar'

4. Install Android emulator
   a. If not mounted, mount the USB (/media/debian/data)
   b. Download Android SDK:
      https://github.com/youngmin-kim-tfs/gsd-debian-aosp/releases/download/android-sdk/android.tgz
   b. Untar android.tgz to /dev/sda3
      - sudo tar zxvf /media/debian/data/android.tgz -C /data
   c. Change to /data/android/avd
   d. In SeqStudio.ini, set path to /data/android/avd/SeqStudio.avd
   e. Launch the emulator:
      - ANDROID_SDK_HOME=/data/android sdk/emulator/emulator -avd SeqStudio -no-snapshot


